OL,3,CMum's knife scanner plea at school
OL,4,Cwhere son was stabbed to death
OL,6,FThey stopped to look at tributes
OL,7,Foutside the school gates before going
OL,8,Finto the grounds to see a collection
OL,9,Fof more flowers and tributes.
OL,11,FMrs Willgoose said she had been
OL,12,F"living on autopilot" since her son's
OL,13,Fdeath and made a call for knife arches
OL,14,F- metal detecting scanners - to be
OL,15,Finstalled in every school.
OL,17,FShe said: "I've got to do this for
OL,18,FHarvey and other children... We've got
OL,19,Fto protect them, we've got to make
OL,20,Fthem safe, it's got to stop."
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G2/8
